de.esoco.process.ui.graphics

Class UiImageData

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.esoco.process.ui.UiElement<E>
      • de.esoco.process.ui.UiImageDefinition<UiImageData>
        • de.esoco.process.ui.graphics.UiImageData

  • public class UiImageData
extends UiImageDefinition<UiImageData>
    An image that is defined from the actual image data. The main constructor UiImageData(MimeType, Supplier) accepts a supplier function for the image data that is only evaluated just before application to a component. That allows it to be used for lazy image initialization.

      • UiImageData

        public UiImageData(MimeType eMimeType,
                   java.util.function.Supplier<java.lang.String> fImageData)
        Creates a new instance that receives the image data from a function. The function will be evaluated only just before the image needs to be displayed. That allows this constructor to be used for lazy initialization of images.
        Parameters:
        eMimeType - The MIME type of the image
        fImageData - The function that provides the image data

      • UiImageData

        public UiImageData(MimeType eMimeType,
                   java.lang.String sImageData)
        Creates a new instance from an image data string. The image data can either be Base64 encoded data for binary images or an SVG image description. In the latter case the MIME type must be MimeType.IMAGE_SVG.
        Parameters:
        eMimeType - The MIME type of the image
        sImageData - The image data string
